    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "3 Nephi",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 11,
        "summary": "The Father testifies of His Beloved Son\u2014Christ appears and proclaims His Atonement\u2014The people feel the wound marks in His hands and feet and side\u2014They cry Hosanna\u2014He sets forth the mode and manner of baptism\u2014The spirit of contention is of the devil\u2014Christ's doctrine is that men should believe and be baptized and receive the Holy Ghost. About A.D.\u00a034.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And now it came to pass that there were a great multitude gathered together, of the people of Nephi, round about the temple which was in the land Bountiful; and they were marveling and wondering one with another, and were showing one to another the great and marvelous change which had taken place.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 3:14 (9, 14).",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 22:29; 3\u00a0Ne. 3:23.",
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 155
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 8:12 (11\u201314).",
                        "start": 249,
                        "end": 254
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they were also conversing about this Jesus Christ, of whom the sign had been given concerning his death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 14:20 (20\u201327); 3\u00a0Ne. 8:5 (5\u201325).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that while they were thus conversing one with another, they heard a voice as if it came out of heaven; and they cast their eyes round about, for they understood not the voice which they heard; and it was not a harsh voice, neither was it a loud voice; nevertheless, and notwithstanding it being a small voice it did pierce them that did hear to the center, insomuch that there was no part of their frame that it did not cause to quake; yea, it did pierce them to the very soul, and did cause their hearts to burn.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 4:33; Ezek. 1:24; Hel. 5:29 (28\u201336).",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 19:12 (11\u201313); D&C 85:6.",
                        "start": 317,
                        "end": 322
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 3:11; Jer. 20:9.",
                        "start": 336,
                        "end": 342
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that again they heard the voice, and they understood it not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 1:24 (24\u201328); 1\u00a0Cor. 14:2.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again the third time they did hear the voice, and did open their ears to hear it; and their eyes were towards the sound thereof; and they did look steadfastly towards heaven, from whence the sound came.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 36:15; D&C 101:92.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And behold, the third time they did understand the voice which they heard; and it said unto them:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold my Beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased, in whom I have glorified my name\u2014hear ye him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 3:17; 17:5; JS\u2014H 1:17. TG\u00a0Witness of the Father.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 9:15.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass, as they understood they cast their eyes up again towards heaven; and behold, they saw a Man descending out of heaven; and he was clothed in a white robe; and he came down and stood in the midst of them; and the eyes of the whole multitude were turned upon him, and they durst not open their mouths, even one to another, and wist not what it meant, for they thought it was an angel that had appeared unto them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 12:6; 2\u00a0Ne. 26:1 (1, 9); Alma 16:20; Ether 3:17 (17\u201318).",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 1:9 (9\u201311).",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p8",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that he stretched forth his hand and spake unto the people, saying:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, I am Jesus Christ, whom the prophets testified shall come into the world.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And behold, I am the light and the life of the world; and I have drunk out of that bitter cup which the Father hath given me, and have glorified the Father in taking upon me the sins of the world, in the which I have suffered the will of the Father in all things from the beginning.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Light of the World.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 18:11.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 1:29.",
                        "start": 159,
                        "end": 165
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 14:36 (32\u201342); Luke 22:42; John 6:38; Hel. 10:4; D&C 19:2.",
                        "start": 230,
                        "end": 234
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that when Jesus had spoken these words the whole multitude fell to the earth; for they remembered that it had been prophesied among them that Christ should show himself unto them after his ascension into heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 16:20.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 145
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 10:19.",
                        "start": 176,
                        "end": 180
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that the Lord spake unto them saying:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Lord.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p13",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Arise and come forth unto me, that ye may thrust your hands into my side, and also that ye may feel the prints of the nails in my hands and in my feet, that ye may know that I am the God of Israel, and the God of the whole earth, and have been slain for the sins of the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 20:27.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 24:39 (36\u201339); D&C 129:2.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 45:3; 3\u00a0Ne. 15:5; D&C 36:1; 127:3.",
                        "start": 183,
                        "end": 186
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 9:29; 1\u00a0Ne. 11:6.",
                        "start": 223,
                        "end": 228
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that the multitude went forth, and thrust their hands into his side, and did feel the prints of the nails in his hands and in his feet; and this they did do, going forth one by one until they had all gone forth, and did see with their eyes and did feel with their hands, and did know of a surety and did bear record, that it was he, of whom it was written by the prophets, that should come.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 18:25. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Appearances, Postmortal.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 429
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when they had all gone forth and had witnessed for themselves, they did cry out with one accord, saying:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hosanna! Blessed be the name of the Most High God! And they did fall down at the feet of Jesus, and did worship him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worship.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that he spake unto Nephi (for Nephi was among the multitude) and he commanded him that he should come forth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 1:2 (2\u20133, 10); 7:15 (15, 20, 23).",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p18",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Nephi arose and went forth, and bowed himself before the Lord and did kiss his feet.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 34:8; Ether 6:12.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 17:10.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord commanded him that he should arise. And he arose and stood before him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 7:10; Ezek. 2:1 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord said unto him: I give unto you power that ye shall baptize this people when I am again ascended into heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Church Organization; Priesthood, Authority.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Essential.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again the Lord called others, and said unto them likewise; and he gave unto them power to baptize. And he said unto them: On this wise shall ye baptize; and there shall be no disputations among you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 12:7; 3\u00a0Ne. 12:1.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 11:16 (16\u201319); 3\u00a0Ne. 18:34. TG\u00a0Disputations.",
                        "start": 176,
                        "end": 191
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p22",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Verily I say unto you, that whoso repenteth of his sins through your words, and desireth to be baptized in my name, on this wise shall ye baptize them\u2014Behold, ye shall go down and stand in the water, and in my name shall ye baptize them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 26:15 (15\u201316); 3\u00a0Ne. 12:2.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Qualifications for.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 19:11 (10\u201313).",
                        "start": 180,
                        "end": 185
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p23",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now behold, these are the words which ye shall say, calling them by name, saying:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Having authority given me of Jesus Christ, I baptize you in the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Ghost. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 18:13; Alma 5:3; D&C 20:73. TG\u00a0Delegation of Responsibility; Priesthood, Authority.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godhead.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And then shall ye immerse them in the water, and come forth again out of the water.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 6:52. TG\u00a0Baptism, Immersion; Jesus Christ, Types of, in Memory.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And after this manner shall ye baptize in my name; for behold, verily I say unto you, that the Father, and the Son, and the Holy Ghost are one; and I am in the Father, and the Father in me, and the Father and I are one.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 11:44; 3\u00a0Ne. 28:10; Morm. 7:7; D&C 20:28.",
                        "start": 139,
                        "end": 142
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And according as I have commanded you thus shall ye baptize. And there shall be no disputations among you, as there have hitherto been; neither shall there be disputations among you concerning the points of my doctrine, as there have hitherto been.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 4:32; 1\u00a0Cor. 1:10 (10\u201313); Eph. 4:13 (11\u201314); D&C 38:27. TG\u00a0Disputations.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For verily, verily I say unto you, he that hath the spirit of contention is not of me, but is of the devil, who is the father of contention, and he stirreth up the hearts of men to contend with anger, one with another.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Tim. 2:24 (23\u201324); Mosiah 23:15. TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 4:27 (26\u201327); Mosiah 2:32 (32\u201333); Alma 2:5; 45:23; Hel. 4:1.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, this is not my doctrine, to stir up the hearts of men with anger, one against another; but this is my doctrine, that such things should be done away.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 9:50; John 16:33.",
                        "start": 137,
                        "end": 143
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 430
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, verily, verily, I say unto you, I will declare unto you my doctrine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 18:37; 2\u00a0Ne. 31:21 (2\u201321).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And this is my doctrine, and it is the doctrine which the Father hath given unto me; and I bear record of the Father, and the Father beareth record of me, and the Holy Ghost beareth record of the Father and me; and I bear record that the Father commandeth all men, everywhere, to repent and believe in me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Teaching Mode of.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 5:7 (6\u20139). TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Relationships with the Father.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 28:11; Ether 5:4; Moses 1:24.",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 173
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And whoso believeth in me, and is baptized, the same shall be saved; and they are they who shall inherit the kingdom of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 16:16. TG\u00a0Baptism, Essential.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation, Plan of.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Exaltation.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And whoso believeth not in me, and is not baptized, shall be damned.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Verily, verily, I say unto you, that this is my doctrine, and I bear record of it from the Father; and whoso believeth in me believeth in the Father also; and unto him will the Father bear record of me, for he will visit him with fire and with the Holy Ghost.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ether 4:12.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 9:20; 12:2.",
                        "start": 225,
                        "end": 229
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Baptism of.",
                        "start": 248,
                        "end": 258
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thus will the Father bear record of me, and the Holy Ghost will bear record unto him of the Father and me; for the Father, and I, and the Holy Ghost are one.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Source of Testimony.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godhead; Unity.",
                        "start": 157,
                        "end": 160
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again I say unto you, ye must repent, and become as a little child, and be baptized in my name, or ye can in nowise receive these things.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 10:15; Luke 18:17.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 9:22.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again I say unto you, ye must repent, and be baptized in my name, and become as a little child, or ye can in nowise inherit the kingdom of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Baptism, Qualifications for.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Verily, verily, I say unto you, that this is my doctrine, and whoso buildeth upon this buildeth upon my rock, and the gates of hell shall not prevail against them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 4:2.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:24 (24\u201329); 1\u00a0Pet. 2:6 (4\u20138); 1\u00a0Ne. 13:36. TG\u00a0Rock.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 16:18; 3\u00a0Ne. 18:13 (12\u201313); D&C 17:8.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And whoso shall declare more or less than this, and establish it for my doctrine, the same cometh of evil, and is not built upon my rock; but he buildeth upon a sandy foundation, and the gates of hell stand open to receive such when the floods come and the winds beat upon them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 16:17 (17\u201319); 1\u00a0Tim. 1:3.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 14:26 (24\u201327).",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 166
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore, go forth unto this people, and declare the words which I have spoken, unto the ends of the earth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}